
Running an Android x86 9 (Pie) VM in Virtualbox
Download Android x86 9 Pie Download
Launch Virtualbox
Create a New VM by selecting Machine > New
Name: Android x86 9 Pie
Machine Folder: C:\VMs
Type: Linux
Version: Other Linux (64-bit)
Memory Size: 2048 MB
Hard disk: Create a virtual hard disk now

Click Create
On the Create Virtual Hard Disk dialog
Name the virtual disk image Android x86 9 Pie.vdi
File size: 16 GB
Hard disk file type: VDI
Storage on physical hard disk: Dynamically Allocated

Click Create
Select the VM and Click Settings
Select System > Processor
Give the VM at least 2 processors
Select the Acceleration tab
Change the Paravirtualization Interface to KVM
Select Display
Slide the Video Memory to 128 MB
Set the Graphics Controller option to VBoxSVGA
Select Network
Set the attached to dropdown to Bridged Adapter
Select Storage
Click on the CD-ROM drive
Select the disc dropdown to the right > Choose a virtual optical disc file...
Browse to and select the downloaded Android x86 .iso file
Click OK
Make sure the Android x86 9 Pie VM is selected and click Start > Normal
At the Android x86 Live & Installation CD screen select Advanced Options... > Press Enter
Select the Auto Installation option > Press Enter
Select Yes to confirm > Press Enter
At the Congratulations dialog, make sure Run Android x86 is selected and press Enter
Complete the Android setup
Welcome to Android 9 Pie
